inn1.comm: Vinay Kumar gets things going, short of length ball that stayed a touch low, Simmons defends off the back foot, hit low on the bat
length ball on the pads, clipped towards midwicket
length ball heading for middle and off, off the inside-half of the bat towards square leg
another length ball on off stump, tucked towards midwicket
nice and tight from Vinay, just outside off, punched off the front foot towards cover
shorter this time, same line around off, defended towards off stump, the crowd gets a bit excited as Raina scores a direct hit
Umesh begins his spell with a short of length ball moving a touch away after pitching outside off, left alone
stands tall and punches this length ball towards cover
gets nicely forward and blocks a delivery that swings a bit away, fielded at point
Hyatt goes for the drive and he is beaten, pitched up by Umesh and gets the ball to move away a bit., nicely done
shorter this time but the result is the same, Hyatt looks to drive through the off and is beaten, this time he attempted the shot off the back foot
length ball on middle and leg, defended towards midwicket to complete a maiden
Vinay hasn't got the ball to jag around but he has kept it around off every time, this time Simmons defends back to the bowler
pitched up, again not much width, Simmons leans across and drives towards cover
a wild shot from Simmons, looks to muscle the ball down the ground, mistimes it towards mid-on

the end of Simmons? the umpires are conferring about a caught-behind chance, they want the third umpire to confirm the edge carried to the keeper, it was a short of length ball that is a slightly wider than the previous two deliveries, Simmons fishes at it outside off, definite edge, many replays needed here, on the first replay I thought it landed on Parthiv's fingers, the third umpire wants about a dozen replays to be sure, and he finally decides that carried, a rare ODI failure for Simmons this year
short of length and outside off and that is left alone by Samuels
on the bounce to second slip, it was just outside off, Samuels pushed at it late, off the face off the bat, bravely trying to steer it past second slip, can't
blocked solidly down the track
more defence, this time towards cover off the front foot, 14 balls since a run was scored
make that 15, short of length round middle, pushed towards mid-on without much power
the fuller one from Umesh, gets the ball to swing in a touch, the bat face was open as Hyatt played that, he managed to keep it out though
gets movement again, a length ball, Hyatt is chest-on as he defends that one
a wonderful shot to end the dot-ball streak, short of length and outside off, hangs back  and chops that in front of point for four, nicely done by Hyatt
played down towards third man for an easy single
off the inside-half of the bat as Hyatt looks to punch this back of length delivery off the back foot, the ball dribbles towards mid-on
length ball just outside off, driven towards point off the front foot
solidly defended off the front foot, back towards the bowler
punched towards cover off the front foot this time
the final ball of the over is a touch sort, guided towards backward point, vinay's figures are now 	3-1-3-1
a low full toss on off stump, bunted back towards the bowler
length ball outside off, Samuels is happy to allow that to the keeper
tapped towards point by Samuels, but there's no run to be had
that slower one swings in for Umesh, pitched up on middle and leg, defended from the crease by Samuels
well outside off, Samuels patiently watches it go through to the keeper
squeezes this one down to third man for a single and keeps the strike
throws his bat at that one though there isn't oo much width available, powerfully slapped towards point, but the placement isn't very good
beaten, that stayed lower than Samuels expected, a length ball that Samuels decides to play by staying on the crease without moving forward or back, pokes his bat at it, doesn't connect
mild appeal for lbw, as Samuels strides forward and edges the ball on to his pads
Samuels likes the third man area, backs away to make room and opens the face to guide the ball for a single
pushed to the left of mid-off and the batsmen scamper a single
length ball on off stump, defended off the front foot to the off side, another quiet over comes to an end
a muted appeal for lbw, the ball snakes down the leg side, takes the pad towards fine leg
full ball just outside off, a mistimed drive towards mid-off, Mithun can't stop it as he tries to field
length ball outside off, guided down to third man once again for a single
punched towards mid-off this time, another dot ball

a boundary, Samuels is tired of waiting and watching, he nearly lost his wicket there, he wanted to loft it over the infield, and just about manages to do that, the ball lobs over mid-off lands just outside the inner circle before racing for four
two in a row, stands tall and lashes that in front of point, played on the up that shot, 11 off the over, more than doubles the total, not a good start for Mithun
a length ball on middle stump, punched towards deep midwicket for three, not much power behind that stroke from Hyatt
short of length ball outside off, Samuels looks to glide it past backward point but Kohli dives to his left to stop that
bottom hand comes off the bat as he defends a middle stump ball towards the off side, played from within the crease
powerfully struck by Samuels, a misfield by Gambhir at mid-on, the ball dribbles towards the boundary and mid-off has to field
length ball outside off, batsman opens the face to guide the ball towards backward point
glides it down to third man for a single to end the over
back of length ball on offstump, fended towards cover by Samuels
a length ball outside off, a crisp drive towards cover where Raina dives to the right to cut it off
back of a length ball on off stump, pushed towards mid-off, batsman calls early for the single and they take it easily
length ball slides in towards legstump, defended to the leg side
slides it on to the pads once again, clipped towards square leg
on middle and leg, the batsman looks to whip it towards midwicket but edges it on to his pads
on middle stump, batsman shuffles across and tucks it towards square leg
switches to an outside-off line, pushed towards the off side from the crease
hello hello, where did that come from? Hyatt muscles a pull over midwicket for six, it was a short ball from Vinay, not the best move at his pace, Hyatt swatted it away easily
that stays low outside off, Hyatt has to adjust late to poke it to the off side
pushes hard at the ball and gets an edge past his pads and down to fine leg for a single
right on off stump, steered towards backward point, Samuels wanted one and set off, Hyatt didn't and stayed put, a moment of misunderstanding, but Samuels returns back to his crease well in time
length ball on middle, Hyatt moves across and defends to the leg side
looks to glance this delivery down to fine leg but is struck on the pads outside leg stump
the two-eyed stance from Samuels, he defends the ball towards midwicket
length ball outside off, played behind point, and again there is confusion in the running, again they realise early enough to return back to the crease
whipped off the pads towards deep midwicket
short of a length and in the channel outside off, pushed towards cover to end the over
big appeal for lbw, but the inside-edge saves him, Samuels looks to defend out the front foot, bat a little away from his pad
much more solid defence from Samuels this time
gets nicely forward and drives towards mid-off for a single
slapped hard towards short cover, where Raina is lurking
drops it short but gets away with it, carefully pushed back towards the bowler
strays on to the pads, batsman glances it down towards fine leg for a single

looked like a gutterball but has turned into a strike, Mithun slides it down the leg side, Hyatt shuffles across and looks to send that to fine leg, gets a thin edge, Parthiv gets a second catch, Hyatt should be furious with himself for getting out in this fashion, especially with the thin West Indian batting, a first ODI wicket for Mithun
short of length ball around middle and off, defended off the front foot towards cover
keeps bat and pad close together as he defends that down the track
outside off, and Bravo is happy to leave
length ball on the pads, tucked past midwicket for a couple,  Bravo is on his way
a full delivery that Bravo defends solidly off the front foot
just outside off, Samuels stretches forward and blocks it
tossed up and more defence from Samuels
gets on the back foot and defends it towards backward point
pushed towards point by Samuels

massive appeal for caught-behind, it was the arm ball, Samuels was on the back foot looking to cut, that sneaks past, Samuels was quite late playing that, Parthiv and Jadeja bring the house down with the appeal, umpire's finger stays down as well
blocked towards point to end the over
on middle and off, blocked towards midwicket
punches this one on the up, can't get it past the man at extra cover
gets inside the line and guides the ball towards third man for a single
homing in on offstump, length ball, Samuels pushes the ball back towards the bowler
short of length ball, Samuels backs away and carves it towards sweeper cover for a couple, not the most well-timed of strokes
back of a length ball, blocked back to the bowler
starts with a delivery down the leg side, helped along towards fine leg for a single
Samuels backs away, exposing all three stumps, bottom hand comes off as he defends that middle stump delivery to the off side
fuller delivery from Umesh, Samuels looks to hammer that one, connects well but can't place it past mid-off

this time he gets it past mid-off, a fuller ball is driven to the left of a diving mid-off for a boundary, Samuels doesn't care too much about getting his feet in the right place, just goes with his hands and connects well this time
a slightly slower one from Umesh, Samuels manages to keep that out
Samuels has been itching to back away to make room and slash the ball through the off side, bottom-edges this one on to his pads, and that's drinks
no room at all for Bravo, this time it's on off stump, Bravo defends
flat-batted by Bravo for four, does Lara play that shot? it was played uppishly and past mid-off for a boundary, a length ball outside off, not much wrong with it
on middle and leg this, careful defence
on middle stump, opens the face to play that towards point
short of length and on the pads, easy runs for Bravo, moves across and nudges the ball towards square leg for a couple
defended to the off side off the front foot
Samuels gets hold of this one, a short of length ball, Samuels gets the front leg well out of the way and clouts the ball over long-on for six
swings this to the square leg boundary for four, it was short from Umesh and it sat up for Samuels, so that's 10 off the first two deliveries
a fuller ball that Samuels wants to dispatch over mid-on, played uppishly but lands sort of the fielder at mid-on
Samuesl has decided everything-must-go, it was slow and short, well outside off stump, samuels cracks that past point for a boundary, 14 off the over
just outside off, Samuels guides it towards third man for a single
length ball on the pads, clipped to square leg for a single
Ashwin starts with a wide down the leg side
blocked down the track
once again it is defended back towards the bowler
clips this towards midwicket for a single
Samuels stays back though the length isn't too short, gets it away towards cover for a single
punched towards mid-on by Bravo

off the pads and towards short fine, Jadeja has a direct hit as Bravo plonks his bat in the crease after deciding there's no run, Gavaskar would have gone ballistic if he was on TV commentary, replays show Bravo has brought his bat down in time
first ball of the over is pushed towards cover
an appeal for lbw, but that was solidly defended
spins away after pitching outside off, Samuels taps it behind point and takes a quick single, that can't be good for Bravo's hamstring
rocks back and chops the ball towards point, Bravo is struggling here, hobbling as he takes the single, no runners
a big appeal for lbw, but there was a big inside edge there
no appeal, no inside-edge, that was off the middle of the bat as he defended
stays on the back foot and looks to punch the ball towards cover, bottom-edges it towards the off side
makes better contact this time, sends it behind point
comes forward and defends back to the bowler
tossed up, length delivery that is driven down to long-off, Bravo limps a single

run-out missed, Samuels stands tall and punches the ball, Ashwin fields behind the stumps, Bravo was yards down the ground and even if he was fully fit, he would have never made it back, Ashwin misses by a big margin as he tries to throw down the stumps, Ashwin perhaps had time to wait for Jadeja to come to the stumps, and then attempting the run-out
blocks the last ball of the over towards point
solidly defended by Bravo
Bravo has had enough of running, smacks a full ball to long-on for four
played towards mid-on for an easy single
Samuels gets well forward and defends to the off side
shows the full face of the bat as he blocks
helped to sweeper cover for a single
on middle and leg, clipped to square leg
length ball on legstump, defended towards the leg side
why are they attempting these sharp singles when Bravo is clearly struggling to run between the wickets? Samuels clips it to short midwicket and sets off
Bravo is looking for the boundaries now, he goes for a big heave, sends the ball towards long-on
Samuels gets well forward and blocks the final ball of the over
just outside off, Bravo rocks back and carves it to backward point
on the pads, whipped to short midwicket
just outside off, squeezed to short third man for a single
the 50 partnership comes up, Samuels eases the ball towards long-on for a single
length ball, Bravo looks to drive, mistimes it back to the bowler
Jadeja drops it short, Bravo looks to club that over midwicket, doesn't connect too well, gets the ball away to deep square leg
length ball on middle and leg, a line Ashwin has adopted against Bravo, pushed back to the bowler
backs away and punches the ball towards extra cover, where Raina makes a smart stop
well outside off, Bravo can't capitalise, he's looking for the booming shot but misses
stands tall and punches the ball towards long-off to get a couple
length ball around off, Bravo stays on the back foot, plays with a flat bat, sends the ball towards long-off again
gently done by Samuels, leaning forward and guiding the ball in front of point for a single
a length ball outside off, defended off the front foot
slaps it in front of point for a single
a length ball spinning towards off, solid forward defence
and again, Raina being accurate here, driven towards short midwicket
Ramdin gets going with a boundary, he was given a bit of room, chops it past deep point for a boundary, playing it late to get the placement right
reverts to forward defence to end the over
whips this off the pads towards midwicket
a length ball, Samuels stands tall and pushes the ball back to the bowler
more forward defense from Samuels
on middle stump, keeping Samuels quiet again
tossed up, slightly shorter, gets the ball to turn a bit, clipped to midwicket
short of a length and just outside off, punched towards long-off for a single
driven off the front foot, Raina moves to his right to cut it off
looking to cut the ball though the ball was turning in a touch,  bottom-edged to the leg side
makes room and stabs this towards backward point
defended towards midwicket
full ball on the pads, nudged to midwicket
there's his fifty, eased down to long-off for a single, Samuels reaches half-century No. 22
length ball on middle, defended to the leg side
outside off this time, steps forward and gets it away towards point for one
pushed off the front foot towards point for a single
length ball outside off, drives firmly to the right of sweeper cover, enough time to get two
round the wicket, that's on the pads, blocked to the leg side
length ball on middle and leg, defended down the track
length ball is punched towards long-on for a single
driven to mid-on, no run this time
fuller ball, on middle and leg, tucked to  midwicket
Jadeja dives to his left at short cover after Samuels crashes the ball off the back foot, keeps them to a single
worked to deep midwicket for a single
pushed towards long-off for a single to end the over, India getting through their overs quickly here
round the wicket, on the pads, helped towards mid-on for one more
shorter this time, again driven to the leg side, long-on this time
tossed up, full and on middle and off, eased towards long-off for one more, no risks from the West Indians at this stage
solid forward defensive this time
down the leg side, nudged towards square leg, there's a quick call of 'No'
pitched up just outside off, guided towards backward point to end the over
driven just past the bowler, who gets a hand on it but can't stop it completely
short of length ball just outside off, Ramdin was rushing out for a single, had to rush back to beat the throw as Samuels wasn't interested
whips it in front of square leg
pushed to the right of the bowler, Raina gets across to stop that
pitched up, on middle stump, easy single to long-on
short of length, on middle and off, punched off the back foot towards extra cover
Ashwin continues with his length ball aournd leg, carrom ball this time, off the leading edge to the off side
defended to the leg side by Ramdin
Ashwin keeps it on the pads, worked towards deep square leg
Samuels is gone, making room early on to go for the expansive drive, Ashwin skids it through and the off stump is pegged back, once again the Batting Powerplay proves dangerous to the batting team
over the wicket now, a length ball on the pads,defended

fuller and around off, pushed towards cover, Gambhir fumbles and Mithun has to change direction to try stop the ball, Mithun seems to have hurt himself while fielding that,  some problem with his leg, the physio comes out
Jadeja returns, Pollard reaches for a length ball and drives it to the right of Jadeja
not the best of shots that, a length ball that Pollard threw his bat at, inside-edged towards midwicket, he wanted to hammer that one
pushed off the front foot towards wide mid-on, Jadeja has to run across to field
quicker one heading for off and middle, blocked to the leg side
helped towards long-on for a single
slides on with the arm towards leg, pushed towards long-on for a single to end the over
Ashwin round the wicket, keeps attacking the pads, clipped towards midwicket
flighted delivery, spins in after pitching outside off, defended off the front foot
the carrom ball, defended down the track by the batsman
length ball on middle stump, whipped towards square leg
another easy single, guided towards long-on
too far down the leg side from Ashwin
length ball on the pads, defended to the leg side, just two off the over, not much of a 'power'play this for West Indies
long-on has been kept busy when the spinners are bowling, another single there
arm ball goes down the leg side
length ball, flat and around off and middle, defended off the front foot
bit of an inside-edge as Pollard attempts the forward defensive
a touch shorter from Jadeja, heading for middle stump, punched towards long-on
on the pads again, Ramdin shuffles across and manages to get it fine, beats Ashwin at short fine leg, Ashwin gives chase but the ball wins the race
off the pads and just behind the keeper
Raina round the wicket, flat and full outside off, Pollard can't connect
on the pads this time, clipped towards midwicket
short from Raina, Ramdin stays back and slaps the ball to long-on
short of length ball on middle and leg, Mithun (who has just returned to the field), dives and stops it at mid-off
and the familiar single to long-on once again
on the pads, tucked towards square leg for one more
Jadeja spears it in towards middle and leg, turned to the leg side

Gambhir drops it at midwicket, he's had a poor day in the field, this was sitter, Pollard wanted to club that one, can't get hold of it, a thick inside-edge,  and it comes to Gambhir chest high, not too fast either, how did he drop that one?
nearly a run-out now after Pollard pokes the ball towards point for a tight single
works it down to fine leg for a single
Pollard looking for a big hit over midwicket again, another mishit, wide of Gambhir though this time
eased towards long-on for a single
slides this across from round the wicket, Ramdin goes for the off drive off the front foot and is beaten
length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler
punched towards long-off for an ambled single
manages to chip that over the bowler's head, Pollard can't time it all all here, no footwork as he swings his bat at that
the cut is a shot Ramdin is very comfortable playing, he backs away and chops it towards deep backward point for a single
at long last success for Pollard, after many mistimed shots, he finally gets hold of one, stays back and clouts a shortish ball from Raina over midwicket for six, the 150 comes up
driven towards short extra cover by Ramdin
slaps this one towards sweeper cover for a single
flat delivery, length and just outside off, poked to the off side
more flight this time, another length ball, pushed back to the bowler
hangs back and looks to slug it to long-off, can't beat a diving Jadeja
another flat delivery to end the over, slaps it towards deep point for a single
looks to pull that one, bottom-edges it to the leg side
short of length ball outside off, flies off the bat towards third man for a single
where was Pollard going? he drops the ball towards the bowler and sets off for a run, has to turn around and race back as Umesh was on to the ball quickly
that would have gone out of the stadium if he connected, instead Pollard fresh-airs it, and the ball goes through to the keeper
short of a length and on the pads, cleverly done by Pollard, the big hit didn't come off but he just worked that wide of a diving short fine leg for a boundary, hardly any effort behind that stroke
full and well outside off, helped towards point for a single to end the over
Jadeja's last over, a full, flat ball outside off, jabbed towards short third
length ball on the pads, clipped towards midwicket and sprints two
length ball on offstump, poked towards cover for a single
a bit of flight to Ramdin, who look to carve the ball through off, bottom-edges it towards cover
length ball angling into the pads, nudged towards square leg
flat and short, heading for middle, Pollard stretches his giant leg forward and shows off a tight front-foot defense
the cut is productive once again for Ramdin, width from Umesh, slashes wide of deep backward point for four
length ball closer to the stumps, pushed towards point for only a single, 50 stand comes up, partnerships haven't been the problem for them, it's the run-rate
bangs in the bouncer, Pollard goes for the pull, top-edge well over the keeper, bounces once before going for four
a yorker just outside off, nicely negotiated by Pollard, guides it down to third man for a single
third catch for Parthiv, Ramdin is gone, Umesh rolls the fingers to take off the pace, again it is a little wide outside off, Ramdin looks to slash it through the off, nicks it to Parthiv
short of length ball outside off, Umesh gets the outside edge, would have been gobbled up if there was a first slip, there isn't one, and Russell is off the mark with a boundary, 14 off the over
almost a yorker, just outside off, Pollard opens the face but can't get bat on ball, through to the keeper

Jadeja has pulled off a blinder here!, the end of Pollard, it was a poor delivery from Vinay, a length hit-me delivery, Pollard hits it, but not flat enough to clear the ropes, it goes miles high, and then drops towards the deep extra cover boundary, Ravindra Jadeja runs towards it from long-off, had plenty of ground to make but manages to cover it and latches on to it, tumbling over as he completes the catch, outstanding effort that
blocked off the front foot by Russell
short of length ball on off stump, pushed towards cover for a single
a low full toss is clouted over cover for four, Sammy is off the mark
sweeper cover has to do the fielding after Sammy punches the ball
short of length ball, heading outside off, slapped towards midwicket
plenty of width there, Russell slaps it over backward point for four, that's the first boundary off Ashwin's bowling today
looks to clear deep midwicket here, but the big hit doesn't go all the way, lands short of the fielder
the paddle-sweep goes awry, the ball trickles towards cover instead as Sammy attempts the shot too early
full ball just outside off, Russell is beaten as he looks to drive
a muscular sweep as Ashwin's final delivery is on the leg stump
short of length ball angling in, inside-edged on to his right knee by Russell, who is hobbling as takes the single, just above the knee actually
crisp strike that, brings up the 200, a full toss outside off,  Sammy powers it to the deep extra cover boundary
muscles this down the ground, towards long-off

comic cricket this! Russell jumps across the crease very very early and then goes back to his normal stance, Vinay tries to bowl it wide of offstump but the attempted slower ball goes completely wrong, barely on the pitch as it bounces through to the keeper
top fielding from Rohit at long-on, clouted down the ground by Russell, plenty of power on that shot
slow and wide outside off, Sammy waits on it and steers the ball to the deep backward point boundary, a productive over this, third man can't come across to stop that
guides the final ball of the over to third man for a single
length ball that is sweetly timed by Sammy, can't beat Gambhir at extra cover though

slower ball, short of length ball outside off, Sammy is forced to delay his shot, slaps it to backward point would have been tight if there was a direct hit at the keeper's end, the throw from Rohit is wide though
full ball on the pads, chipped towards short midwicket
a high full toss, too high? no say the umpire, Sammy adjusts to that, slams it towards deep midwicket for a single, it was lower than the waist
another slower ball from Yadav, short of length and outside off, Russell goes for the powerful cut but misses
Russell finally gets hold of one, and boy can he hit them, are the IPL scouts watching? he murders this length ball into the stands beyond wide long-on, nice way to end the over for WI
he starts with a wild delivery well outside off
how did Sammy manage to get that away for four, it was full and very very wide, somehow Sammy didn't just reach it, he managed to get enough power on it to chop it past deep backward point for four
another length ball, another swat, another boundary, wide of long-on this time, not the best length from Mithun here
Sammy taking guard outside off, he wanted to launch this dot ball out of the park, doesn't connect and the ball goes through to the keeper
what a shot that is from Sammy! outstanding, again Mithun puts it on a length, width as well, pummelled over cover for six, this is an incredible hit from Sammy
and another one, West Indies building up a decent total here, a full toss on the pads, clubbed over midwicket for six more, lost count of the number of runs this over
another swing, gets the ball to midwicket, should have only been a single, Kohli fields and throws at the non-striker's end, giving away an overthrow

brilliant hit this, Umesh bowls a full delivery, Russell can't get under it but somehow manages to get enough power as he whacks that dead straight, long-on and long-off converge but not quick enough to stop the ball
four more, carnage here, and this was a poor delivery, a nice full toss on leg stump, clubbed past long-on for four
gets the front leg out of the way and swings hard at it, a top edge and that swirls over the infield and towards deep backward point
ten overs ago we were headed for a low-scoring one-sided match, not anymore, thrashes this one towards the commentary box, straight and powerful hit
not  a boundary this time, another muscular hit down the ground, Umesh gets a bott in the way, the ball ricochets toward mid-on, Russell scampers through for two
a near yorker to finish, the best delivery he's bowled this over, slapped towards midwicket for two

inn2.comm: Parthiv defends the first delivery, short of length and on off stump, defended towards cover
stays on the crease and pokes the ball towards point, shouts 'Nooo,' early to let Sehwag know there's no single to be taken
a yorker, on middle and off, Parthiv gets his bat down in time, inside-edges it onto his boot
great way to get off the mark, on the pads, Parthiv times this to the midwicket boundary, two West Indian fielders give chase but can't haul the ball back in time
and again, between midwicket and mid-on this time, wonderfully timed again, once again Raoch pitches it up on the pads, effortless this from Parthiv
short of length ball just outside off, Parthiv raises the bat over his head as he lets the ball through to the keeper

Rampaul gets the dream start, Virender Sehwag gone for a first-baller, it was short of a length and outside off, Sehwag looks to punch that one through the off side, a top-edge result, easy for Ramdin, Rampaul is cock-a-hoop, Sehwag's indifferent ODI form continues

oh boy, this is amazing, Gambhir gets a golden duck now, fails to offer  shot to a delivery that was delivery for off stump, massive lbw appeal and that umpire is convinced, Gambhir was looking to shoulder arms, that one jags in a touch, Rampaul's on a hat-trick now
outside off, and this time safely left alone, no hat-trick of Delhi wickets for Rampaul
outside off, swings away a touch and Kohli is happy to leave again
pitched up outside off, punched towards cover
a fantastic over from Rampaul to start off, a length ball just outside off and Kohli lets it through to the keeper, a double-wicket maiden
the batsmen may have struggled at the other end, but Parthiv is at home here, another gentle push for four, this time he comes down and helps the ball between mid-on and the bowler
the surreal cricket continues, a short of length ball outside off, Parthiv guides it past the slips for his fourth boundary, he's now 16 off 8
another sweetly timed shot, towards extra cover, can't beat the fielder though
Kohli gets on his toes and defends to the leg side
outside off, Kohli punches it confidently towards point
short of a length and outside off, Kohli opens the face to guide the ball towards third man for a single
swinging away after pitching on a length outside off, Kohli shoulders arms
not much away movement this time, still a couple of feet outside off, Kohli content to leave once more
back of a length and on off stump, Kohli drops the ball at his feet
length ball outside off, poked towards third man by Kohli
Parthiv is cramped up for room, this ball swerves in after pitching on middle and off, Parthiv looks to tuck it to square leg, struck on the thigh pad
Parthiv looks to chop a delivery well outside off, but the ball sneaks under his bat
starts with a length ball just outside off, clipped to the leg side
spins in from a length, nothing dramatic, defended off the front foot
cuts away this time, Kohli stays on the back foot  and defends
slapped towards cover this time
spins in towards the pad, defended to the leg side
short of length ball outside leg stump, easy put away for Parthiv, swept fine for four, India move on to 24
Kohli shows the sort of form he is in, a length ball that he carved through cover, opening the face to get the placement right, had to adjust for the away movement as well
this was easy for Kohli, too full from Rampaul, on the pads, a superbly timed on-drive past a diving Andre Russell at wide mid-on, consecutive fours for Kohli
well done by Pollard at point, another crisp punch from Kohli, Pollard moves across to his right and dives to stop that one
pitched up and just outside off, solidly pushed towards cover off the front foot
nicely timed once again by Parthiv, getting forward and pushing the ball towards mid-off, he's looking in good touch but he's shown a penchant for throwing it away after getting  start
angling across, outside off, Parthiv shoulders arms
Narine spins this slightly away after pitching on off, pushed towards point
the offspinner this time, clipped to backward square leg
Kohli gets well back and pushes this back towards the bowler, watching the ball closely
getting the offbreak to turn sharply this time, there has only been gentle turn so far before this delivery, Kohli is struck high on the back pad, but that was spinning down leg
flighted delivery on middle stump, defended to the leg side
goes straight on, Kohli looks to muscle it past mid-off, not the best timing
length ball just outside off, pushed in front of point by Kohli
a bottom-edge, Parthiv doesn't quite know where the ball is after he plays that, frantically searches for it as it bounces next to him and spins away from the stumps, a single is scrambled
confidently defended towards the off side by Kohli, gets well forward as he keeps that out
bangs in the short ball, Kohli stands tall and hooks it powerfully for four, comfortably clears midwicket on its way for four
defended towards cover, thinks about a single but there isn't one
bit of width from Rampaul, Kohli reaches for it and stabs it towards deep backward point, pushes Parthiv into coming back for the second
full ball outside off, slapped towards long-off by Parthiv

Narine has his first international wicket, and it's the big onbe of Kohli, it was a length ball, an offspinner, Kohli looks to play it to the leg side, looked to have been struck on middle stump, umpire was convinced that would have taken leg, Kohli isn't, he doesn't like the decision one bit, but that doesn't matter, he's on his way, that was a tight call
spin in a long way, it was on the shorter side, well outside off, Rohit leaves it outside off
the legcutter, not big turn, defended by Rohit
gets back in the creases and crisply pushes the ball back towards the bowler
pitched up, flatter on, on middle and leg, worked towards midwicket

Parthiv meanwhile is batting on the "highway" Sunil Gavaskar had predicted this track would be, another power-free boundary, gets forward and pushes the ball past the bowler, and wide of Andre Russell at mid-off for four
short of length and just outside off, chopped towards backward point
on the pads this time, Parthiv shuffles across and glances the ball towards short fine leg
pitched up by Roach, Rohit drives towards mid-on where Russell misfields, off his boot towards mid-off
almost a yorker, bowled from wider of the crease, Rohit keeps it out, tucking it to the leg side

a waft from Rohit, that ball swerves away after pitch back of a length, Rohit chases after it but can't connect, bounces a second time before reaching the keeper, who has to dive to his right to stop the ball
spins in from a short of length, tucked to the leg side
defended to the leg side by Rohit
a length ball is pushed back towards the bowler, who has to move to his left to field
the legbreak, just short of a length, defended to the off side by Rohit
whoah! Rohit gets off the mark with an inside-out lofted drive over extra cover for six, didn't try to power that one, all timing after Narine pitched it up
drags back the length a touch, Rohit happy to defend
short of length ball just outside off, Parthiv guides it past slips for a single

wonderful from Rohit, Roach fires it in full, Rohit gets forward and caresses the ball between the bowler and mid-on for four, all along the ground, his two run-scoring strokes so far have been delights
Roach oversteps, Rohit reaches out to a delivery outside off and is beaten

fantastic cricket this, a full delivery flung in by Roach, Rohit gets the front leg out of the way and creams the way powerfully towards the point boundary, four runs seemed a certainty until the substitute Anthony Martin galloped across to stop that one
drives towards Pollard at backward point for a single
Parthiv is happy to defend this one back towards the bowler
blocks this one towards point to end the over
punched off the back foot to the right of the bowler for a single
clipped towards midwicket by Parthiv
drops this one towards cover and pinches a single
spins in from a length, Rohit goes back and punches the ball towards long-on
Parthiv makes a bit of room, pitched up delivery, driven a little uppishly, but there's no mid-off, long-off fields
blocked off the front foot to the off side
shortish ball and down the leg side, Parthiv likes it there, helps that one very fine down the leg side for four, fine leg can't get around
better from Russell, pitching it up, Parthiv defends
length ball around middle, pushed towards mid-on by Parthiv
on the pads once more, freebies these, Parthiv whips it towards deep backward square leg and sprints back for the second
length ball is punched through the in-field, towards sweeper cover for an ambled single
a length ball is pushed towards backward point by Rohit, Russell's speed has been in the low 130s this over
pushed towards long-off for a single
pushed towards cover off the front foot
terrific work from Simmons at cover, Rohit cracked that off the back foot, Simmons leaps to his left to stop that
more work for Simmons, this time he has to move to his right to field
Rohit gets a good stride in, clips the ball in front of square leg for a single, four of those in this over now

hello, hello, where did that come from? wasn't Narine the mystery spinner, Parthiv might not agree right now, Samuels gets one to spin away sharply, Parthiv closes the face looking to play the ball to the leg side, the ball turns past the leading edge and takes the top of off, and once again Parthiv looks good for a short while but doesn't convert it into a substantial score, done enough to get two more games?
lovely stroke from Rohit, gets nicely forward and eases it towards sweeper cover
not as pretty this time, no feet as he chases a ball well outside off, doesn't connect
and again, Rohit lives dangerously, looks to drive off the front foot, gets a thick inside-edge, ball squirts away towards square leg
short of length ball just outside off, shuffles across and defends to the leg side
gets off the mark Raina, pushes it past extra cover, where Hyatt makes an amateurish attempt at fielding the ball

and another one for Rampaul, Raina can't believe the decision, makes it clear he's not happy with the call, shaking his head as he walks off, it was a legstump delivery, Raina move across and jumps as he tries to guide it to fine leg, think it took his thigh pad, Ramdin does well to pouch the chance, diving to his right and plucking it low, he appeals, umpire Tony Hill upholds it, surely West Indies can't lose this now
some width for Rohit, makes room as well and slaps it past point for four
fired in towards leg, tucked to midwicket for a single
solid forward defence from Jadeja
gets nicely forward and block to the off side
a quicker delivery to end the over, pushed back to the right of the bowler
well outside off and that is left alone
length ball outside off, and another leave from Rohit
short of length ball closer to the stumps, Rohit gets on his toes and pushes it behind point
the bouncer takes Jadeja by surprise, struck on the glove by that one, Jadeja though wasn't poking at it, ends up blocking it down the track
well outside off, Jadeja chases that one but doesn't connect
ooh, Narine turns that a long way in, Rohit is cramped up by that one, squeezes it towards midwicket
not much turn this time, goes straight, defended off the front foot
the offpsinner, but not the one which spins dramatically in, defended to the off side, a good test this for Rohit
a legcutter, driven off the back foot towards extra cover, goes past Russell for a single
spins away as Jadeja looks to defend outside off, can't get bat on it
skids straight on, solidly defended by Jadeja
Rohit stands tall and carves this towards sweeper cover for a single
short of length ball outside off, punched towards cover by Jadeja
punched to mid-off, Russell charges in and collects, throws at the non-striker's end, there's no one to back up and an overthrow is taken
short of length delivery outside off, Ravindra Jadeja mistimes the pull back to the bowler

another lbw, the umpire takes a long time before deciding to raise the finger, not sure why Jadeja is hanging around, ah the umpire is going to check for the no-ball, and would you believe it, Rampaul has overstepped, a reprieve for Jadeja, it was a terrific delivery from Rampaul, pitching around leg stump and jagging in, hitting in front of middle and off
free-hit goes for four! Rampaul is dejected, a bouncer dug in, Jadeja goes for the pull, a top-edge over the keeeper's head, one-bounce four, it's a batsman's game alright
four more! no mercy from Jadeja, Rampaul mood dips further, this was a crunching shot, powering a short of length ball outside off past point for a boundary
the offspinner, tucked to square leg for a single
length ball, not turning much, Jadeja defends
shorter, quicker and turning in, Jadeja backs away and slaps the ball towards cover
pitched up around off, Rohit leans forward and pushes the ball back to the bowler

is this a run-out now? Russell is sure it is, Jadeja is walking off, Rohit chops the ball off the back foot towards point, Russell shows off his athleticism once more, onto the ball in a jiffy and releases it quickly, reaches Ramdin on the bounce close to the stumps, he takes off the bails, Jadeja is well short, he had no hope especially after he hesitated early on,six down now, and that elusive first win on tour comes closer for West Indies
Ashwin carefully defends his first delivery, Ian Bishop says "carrom ball  to carrom ball bowler"
looks to power this through off, off the toe of the bat towards mid-off
defended towards mid-on by Rohit
short of length and just outside off, guided down to third man for a single
short ball, Ashwin stands tall and pushes the ball towards point
length ball angling in, "wait in, wait in," is the call after Ashwin drives towards mid-off
nice shot from Ashwin, gets on the backfoot and slices it towards deep backward point
pitched up and that is driven wide of mid-off for a single
spins away from Ashwin, who stays in the crease and pushes the ball towards cover
length ball that is again turning away a hint, Ashwin takes a big stride forward and defends
Ramdin is very vocal even by a wicketkeeper's standards, going ga-ga over every Narine delivery, this was defended solidly by Ashwin
flighted and turning in, driven to mid-on
dropped by Sammy at first slip, the legcutter, Ashwin waits on the back foot and looks to chop that one, edges it to Sammy, who has a low chance but can't latch on, should have been taken
good length delivery outside off, Rohit Sharma comes forward and drives it to mid-off
down the leg side, helped to fine leg for a single
gets forward and punches the ball in front of point, "wait in, wait in," Ashwin says
shortish ball outside off, Ashwin carves it towards point
well outside off, a bit of a bottom-edge as Ashwin slaps the ball towards point

finally he gets it through the gap, and what a graceful shot to get a boundary with, he been looking to play that back foot cut all over, and finally he threads it through the off side to pick up four
stifled appeal for lbw from Sameuls, but there was a big inside-edge from Rohit
stretches forward and turns the ball towards square leg
length ball well wide of the off stump, careful defence off the front foot
"catch him, oh yes, oh yes, lovely bowling," says Ramdin, as the batsman plays the ball a otuch uppishly towards the bowler
Ashwin blocks this one to the leg side
punched towards long-on for a single to end the over
slanting in, a length delivery heading for off, drives off the front foot to the off side
drops it a touch short, steered towards backward point by Ashwin
pitched up this time, Ashwin punches it to sweeper cover for a single

another drop, again it is Sammy, shaking his head in disbelief, Rohit looks to drive a full ball away from his body, outside edge and this one comes straight at Sammy, nice height, no need to move, how did he not catch that?
short of length ball blocked to gully
surprise from Rohit, he charges down and flat bats that over the bowler's head, it was a length ball, not exactly off the middle but there's enough power to get a boundary
gets forward and defends to the leg side
spin and bounce for samuels, Ashwin gets an inside-edge towards backward square leg
driven off the front foot towards point by Rohit
defended to the right of the bowler
spins in from Samuels, Rohit is cramped by it, squeezes it to the leg side, ending a quick and quiet over from Samuels
defended by Ashwin off the front foot to the off side
length ball sliding down the leg side, helped down to fine leg
short of length ball just outside off, guided towards backward point by Ashwin

oh, that would have been the game if mid-on could have reached that, there was no chance of that though, as another inelegant shot from Rohit fetches him a boundary, again flat-batted and just over mid-on before running away for four
full and fired in, dug out to the off side by Rohit
back of a length and around off, driven towards mid-on and Rohit loudly calls "No, no, no"
fuller ball outside, worked wide of mid-on for a single
too wide outside off, quicker one, Rohit reaches out for it and pokes it past slip for four, using the pace
length ball around off, defended towards midwicket
width again, Rohit throws his bat at it, "Catch," screams Ramdin but it is wide of Russell at backward point, deep point fields
fuller ball, worked towards midwicket for a single
length ball just outside off, defended to the leg side
pitched up outside off, driven towards deep extra cover, Rohit comes back for the second, and that's another half-century for Rohit, his sixth against WI
stays back and guides the ball outside off to third man
short ball, leg stump line, Ashwin gets inside the line and helps it along to fine leg
slants it on to the pads, played with soft hands towards square leg for a single
length ball heading for off, driven towards mid-on
tries to squeeze that one under the batsman's bat, Rohit gets the bat down in time, worked towards mid-on
length ball outside off, defended to the leg side by Ashwin
catch is the call again, flicked in the air towards midwicket, which is vacant, gets a single
crisply driven towards cover
a wristy shot sends the ball towards mid-on
a full toss, Samuels lucky India get only a single for that, past a diving fielder in the circle to long-on
on off stump, Ashwin shuffles across and clips the ball behind square leg
nearly chopped on, Rohit tries to cut a delivery that was just outside off, the ball dribbles towards square leg, there's no run initially but an overthrow gives away one
pushed to mid-off for a single
gets away with another low full toss, driven towards long-on for a single
slower ball, Ashwin moves across and tucks the ball behind square leg
too far outside off
slants in towards off, pushed towards long-off for another single, five of them this over
make that six singles in the over, pushed towards long-off for one more
another sensible single, clipping the ball behind square leg
one more, this time towards sweeper cover
another ambled single, to long-on this time
fifty partnership comes up with a couple towards sweeper cover
short of length ball outside off, whacked towards long-on by rohit, who wants the second, Ashwin gets back with no trouble
short of a length ball, Rohit forces this towards midwicket
pushed towards mid-on, a diving stop cut off the singl
length ball outside off, driven towards short extra cover
pitched up, crisply driven, but Simmons gets down in time to stop that one
on the pads, Ashwin plays it backward square leg and takes off, Rohit responds quickly and  completes a tight single
full ball, just outside off, driven to long-off for a single, easy for Rohit
full and well outside off, Ashwin drives towards extra cover but can't get it through the field
short of a length outside off, Rohit stays back and steers his Mumbai Indians team-mate to point.
short and wide, it stays low as Rohit reaches across to cut it in front of square for a single.
legcutter on leg and middle, Rohit works it off the pads to midwicket.
full length legroller outside off, steered through third man for a single.
short of a length, Rohit stays back and works it to midwicket for a single.
Ashwin gets his pad perilously in front of the stumps and works the ball to midwicket for one more.
short of a length on off stump, pushed into the covers for a single.
over-pitched on the pads, Rohit wrists it away to midwicket for a single.
singles are coming everywhere. Wake up, West Indies! Ashwin works another single through midwicket

what a shot! Simmons' trundle at back of a length on off stump doesn't offer pace or room to work with. Rohit creates his own - he moves away to the leg side and clatters it through the covers for four.
fuller length, Rohit works it through midwicket for a single.
ah, wastes a gift on the pads. Ashwin times the whip well, but singles out square leg.
full ball on off stump, Rohit plants it to long off for a single.
sharp offspinner to the sharp offspinner. Ashwin just waits on the crease and drops it towards cover point and picks up an easy single.
tossed up on off, Rohit leans out and wrists it through midwicket for one.
the variation knuckle ball, doesn't quite turn away from back of a length, and Ashwin works it to midwicket.
fuller and on the pads, Ashwin nudges to the leg side but can't get it away.
can't get the single still, so three dots on the row.
poor start. Slants the first ball well down the leg and it is a wide.
full length on the pads, Rohit drives to long-on for one.
well outside off, reaches out for it and guides it down to third man
skips beyond leg, and launches it inside-out over extra cover for a four, easily clears the infield, superb from Rohit
an ordinary delivery from Rampaul, sliding down leg, Rohit should have put that away to the vacant fine leg for four, but its off his thigh pad for a single
sensibly guides this length ball towards midwicket to get another single
four more, Rohit comes down and crashes this behind point for four, a short of length ball which didn't have much wrong, punished by Rohit, nearly a run-a-ball now
defends this one back towards the bowler
overpitched by Samuels, eased towards long-on for a single
you can't drop this guy from the team for a long time now, Rohit picks up another boundary, a touch short from Samuels, Rohit goes back in the crease and powers the ball to sweeper cover
works this to midwicket, Ashwin wants one but is sent back by Rohit
reaches forward and drives it towards deep extra cover
stands tall and drives it towards long-on for a jogged single
spins it in towards the pads, defended to midwicket
full face of the bat as he taps it back to the bowler
spins in a touch, a bit short and that's enough for Ashwin to whip the ball towards deep square leg for a couple
solid forward defensive from Ashwin to a ball outside off
legcutter, Ashwin seems to have read it, punches it back to the bowler

he doesn't read this one, Narine gets rid of Ashwin, pitching on a length just outside off, Ashwin's bat was slow in coming down to meet the offspinner, hit in front of off, no doubts about this decision
spins in towards the batsman, helped to fine leg
outside edge past short third man for a couple
quicker and well outside off, outside edge past short third man for a couple
keeps a bit low, prompting plenty of praise from Ramdin, batsman manages to keep that out
defends this towards square leg
punches it to long-on for a single, keeps the strike and Rohit off it
beaten! a short of length ball angling in, Vinay pokes at it and can't connect, no feet as he played that
wider outside off, and another attempt at a drive through off and again he fresh-airs it

bowled him! Roach hasn't had the greatest of days, but that was the perfect ball to the tailender, a yorker that is too quick and too good for Vinay, the off stump is out of the ground even as Vinay bat comes down
poor delivery to follow the perfect one, wide down the leg side, Mithun's the new batsman
short of length and well outside off, Mithun lets it go
angling in towards middle and leg, Mithun defends it behind point
oh dear! a tailenders swish at that one, fuller ball outside off, no contact, what an over from Roach this is, piles the pressure on Rohit, can he respond?
tremendous stroke from Rohit, gets well forward and cracks that length ball past extra cover for four, he's into the 90s now
defended off the front foot by Rohit
"Two, two, two," Rohit says as soon as he tucks the ball towards deep square leg, terrific from Rohit
taps the ball to long-on and takes the single
spins in from a length, guided towards short third by Mithun

if Rohit had advised Mithun to just play out the over, Mithun clearly hasn't listened to him, a humongous six over long-on, gets under that length ball, clears the front leg, and absolutely hammers it, into the crowd it goes
once again Rohit drives away from his body and doesn't connect
just outside off, Rohit looks to drive, off the outside edge towards third man, takes the single
back of a length ball outside off, confidently opens the face to guide it to third man for a single to give the strike back to Rohit

all is forgiven Sammy, what a bit of fielding this is, ends Rohit's resistance, and the game is surely sewn up now, it wasn't the best of deliveries, a full toss on middle stump, Rohit can only get it as far as wide mid-on, hits it firmly as well, reaches Sammy quickly, the West Indies captain may have dropped a couple of catches today but at this critical juncture, he doesn't fluff it, takes aim and scores a direct hit, Rohit is well short, and he falls short of a hundred as well, it's been a fantastic effort from him though
that seemed like curtains for India, not yet, the yorker is just outside off, whistles through to the keeper
Roach is too quick for the tail,  Mithun swings and misses at one outside off
a thick outside edge gets India a boundary, wide of slip and down to third man
spins in from a length, defended down the track
the legcutter this time, more forward defence
short this time, outside off, blocked towards the off side
driven in the air, "catch," but it is wide of the fielders as it flies towards long-off

Mithun says it ain't over yet, he pummels another six over long-on, a mighty hit from the No. 10, 34 needed now in the final five overs, end of  superb debut for Narine, hardly bowled like a man in his first one-dayer, no sign of nerves even though he was called on to bowl at some tough times
slants in towards off, a length ball, pushed towards mid-on
tries the yorker this time, whipped towards midwicket, can't beat the fielder, Roach has overstepped
a short of length ball, flat-batted hit attempt, horribly mistimed but has enough on it to beat the bowler, a single is taken
a full toss outside off, Roach grunts with the effort as he flings it in, Mithun misses as he attempts to bunt that to the off side
skips beyond leg and looks to whip that to the leg side, Roach can't believe he hasn't hit the stumps, the yorker whistles past leg
a full toss from Roach, Mithun goes for a big swing, ends up slicing it past backward point for four, third man is very fine for a bowler of Roach's pace
full ball on the pads, whips it towards square leg for a couple

the crowd is getting terribly excited now, as Umesh gets another boundary, short of length ball just outside off, Umesh fishes at it and gets a thick outside edge, past third man for four more, Duncan Fletcher in the dressing room is impassive as ever
clips this off the pads for a single, Mithun on strike
four more, Rampaul has his hands on his head after that one, nothing streaky about that,  short of length ball just outside off, wonderfully timed as he guides that behind backward point for four
plenty of confidence in Mithun's batting, gets forward and drives that towards extra cover

West Indies have the win, a massive grin on Gibson's face, it was getting tense but India's record home run in ODIs is over, Rampaul was the man who caused the damage early on, and he's back to finish it off, a yorker strikes the pad in front of the stumps, Rampaul belts out an appeal, and sets off on a celebratory run, though the umpire hasn't raised his finger, it takes Asnani an eternity to rule that out, and West Indies stay alive in this series
